UDM leader Bantu Holomisa has responded to EFF spokesperson Mbuyiseni Ndlozi who said that the Springboks “entrenched white supremacy in the SA society”. Holomisa, who played right wing in his rugby-playing days, said the black players in the World Cup-winning Springbok team were there on merit and that the coaching staff had assembled a good squad and  “deserved a Bell's”.JOIN THE CONVERSATION: For more episodes, click here. Subscribe for free: iono.fm | Spotify | Apple Podcasts | Pocket CastsSay on Twitter at #SportsLIVE